frameDefinitions: An Agent manipulates a Sound_maker or a Cause causes the Sound_maker to emit a sound.
An Entity ends up in a Final_category, Final_situation, or Final_quality which it was not in before.
An Agent acts in a certain Manner either generally or under some particular Circumstances.
Despite some implication that a State would be interrupted, the Entity remains in the specified State.
An Entity ends up with a particular new Final_quality.
An Item comes to be attached to a Goal, with a Connector forming a bond between the Handle of the Item and the Goal (or some part of it).
frameExamples: The monks would <t>ring</t> the bell until sundown.
He pledges to  <t>conduct</t> himself  with honesty and humility.
According to plan, the front part of the hull quietly <t>attached</t> to the docking gear.
listRoleDefinitions: The individual that manipulates a Sound_maker so that it makes Noise.
The entity that produces the Noise, as a result of the action of the Agent.
The inanimate force of nature that causes the <fen>Sound_maker</fen> to produce noise.
The time at which the noise is produced.
The location at which the sound is produced.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which undergoes a change, ending up in the <fen>Final_category</fen>, <fen>Final_situation</fen>, or <fen>Final_quality</fen>.
When the change occurs.
Where the change takes place.
This role marks expressions that denote the person whose conduct is being evaluated.
This role marks expressions that characterize the way that the <fen>Agent</fen> behaves.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> behaves in a certain way.
The location at which the <fen>Agent</fen> exhibits their behavior.
A concrete or abstract <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>State</fen> is found to still persist.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the <fen>State</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which undergoes a change so that it possesses the <fen>Final_quality</fen>.
When the change occurs.
Where the change takes place.
<fen>Connector</fen> identifies the  instrument used to attach, usually in a <ment>with</ment>-PP.
<fen>Item</fen> identifies the entity that comes to be attached to the <fen>Goal</fen>.
<fen>Items</fen> identifies the plural items that are tied together, resulting in their mutual attachment.
<fen>Goal</fen> identifies the location to which the first <fen>Item</fen> is attached.
The time when the attaching event takes place.
The location where the attaching event takes place.
